# Experiment INDEX

List of notebooks, one per **Purpose**, with their hypothesis verdicts and
the Purpose-level conclusion. `scripts/new_experiment.py` adds new entries
automatically.

## Entries

| exp_id | target_sub_claim_id | Purpose (one line) | Hypotheses (H<id>: verdict) | Status | Purpose-level conclusion (one line) |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| exp_001 | G1.0 (foundation) | (example) Define data universe | H1: foundation | done | universe of N instruments × T period defined; data hashes recorded |
| exp_002 | G1.1 | (example) Does PCA factor IC screening yield robust factors? | H2: supported · H3: rejected · H4: parked | done | top-3 PCA factors hold val IC ≥ 0.03 but not on test |
| exp_003 | G1.2 | ... | ... | in-progress | ... |

## Status legend (per notebook)

- `planned`: Purpose stated, notebook not created
- `in-progress`: notebook created, at least one H not yet at a final verdict
- `done`: every H inside the notebook is at a final verdict (supported / rejected / partial / parked) and a Purpose-level conclusion exists
- `parked`: blocked on upstream dependency
- `dropped`: judged not worth pursuing; reason recorded in decisions.md

A notebook is `done` when its Purpose has been answered (per the Purpose-level
synthesis) — not when one specific H is final.

## Order

Sequential numbering, but dependencies (upstream Purposes first) take precedence.
Each notebook states its upstream dependencies in its "Upstream dependencies"
section.
